  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I-- then I wrote in my book, and to keep telling people the story how he got there on the story that I already told, how he was, he was sent in, out, from-- from Sweden, through Germany, through Germany, into Switzerland, to, to, to Dulles, who was the head of the American Secret Service in the Second World War.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There he was briefed, and was given what was sent into Hungary, precisely with this task, of, of, of planning out and convince, convince the Hungarian political and, and military, military leadership in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the Germans in Hungary, a message to Hitler through Hungary.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Let Hitler withdraw his troops from Hungary, pretending that they are retreating ahead of the American army, and the American army moves into Hungary, occupy Hungary, and there be no reason for the Red Army to move further than the, than the, than the Balkans, because in the west, the Western-- Westerm capitalist, and-- and the, and the Chamberlain gang and so on, they were determined, including the British royal family who financed Hitler and the Wallenberg family who financed Hitler very, very heavily.",
      "word_count": 84
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "All that gold that you are hearing there today.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It went into German, the Germans, Germans shipped it out, out to-- to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And from-- to-- to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "From Sweden, they shipped it back, in the form of money and artist back to, back to Hitler, to, to, to arm-- arm Hitler.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it's a problem even--even today.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the army was the, the-- who was, who was, who was a scoundrel, otherwise, George Patton.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And Eisenhower was the, the commander of the unified Western allies army.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
